{
  "texts": [
    "Conversely, Aziz et al. [82] observed a reduction in strength at higher POFA contents (15% and 30%), suggesting that excessive amounts can weaken the cement matrix.",
    "Hussin et al. [79] and Kamaruddin et al.",
    "[27] further highlighted that while low replacement levels (5-20%) can enhance strength, higher levels (15-60%) lead to diminishing returns and potential strength loss.",
    "BentoniteMemon et al. [84] found that while the initial compressive strength decreased, it improved by 2-3% at later ages (28 and 56 days) due to bentonite's pozzolanic properties.",
    "Yang et al. [85] reported substantial increases in both compressive and flexural strengths, particularly at an 8% replacement level."
  ]
}